<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="53" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,464,777]" pageId="3" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,464,489]" pageId="3" pageNumber="53">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Disk with imbricating scales on dorsal and ventral surface (
<figureCitation box="[960,1030,465,489]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[163,1419,843,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,830,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Amphicutis stygobita gen. nov., sp. nov. A, dorsal view disk. B, ventral view disk. C, ventral view arm. D, dorsal view arm. E, side view arm. F, dorsal view arm tip." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205289/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="53">
Fig. 
<number box="[1014,1030,465,489]" pageId="3" pageNumber="53" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Radial shields oval, on disk edge, separated medially along their entire length by one column of disk scales. Second tentacle pore of oral frame outside mouth slit. Genital scales flat and thin, no bursal sacs. Ventral tooth at the apex of each jaw broadly rounded. Proximal oral papillae small rounded, in infradental position. Distal oral papillae oblong, closing off mouth slit with distal oral papilla on adjoining jaw. Small oral papilla sometimes present between infradental and distal papillae. Non-madreporite oral shields small ovals, similar in appearance to disk scales, madreporite distinct. Adoral shields narrow, curved, thin, not tightly fused to oral plates or oral shield. Translucent layer of skin raised above surface of arms in life, usually visible in preservation. Disk and arms often formed mainly by soft tissue outlining plates and scales, but lacking significant calcification.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
